&nbsp;
The following year, O.J. Simpson was sentenced to 9 years for robbery.> His story, among others the New York Times, was a source of inspiration for books, films, studies and debates on justice, racial issues, public exposure of celebrities in a country where these themes are very felt. Today the world press recalls its history: as a poor child and with raking problems, who learned to run away from the police with the teenage bands he was part of in San Francisco, a superpaid football star. In the 1970s he was one of the most famous players in the popular U.S. sports, in the Buffalo Bills with jersey 36. He won the Heisman Trophy and was included in the Hall of Fame of professional football; appeared in dozens of films and commercials for Hertz and other customers; was a sports analyst for ABC and NBC becoming an American idol.
&nbsp;
But then came the dark part of his life: a newborn daughter drowned in the pool, divorce from her high school girlfriend, the grumpy marriage with a beautiful young maid with frequent calls to the police when he beat her; In one case, in 1989, the agents found Nicole Simpson contusa and terrified hidden among the bushes outside the house.&nbsp; Simpson was arrested and convicted of conjugal abuse, but immediately released on probation. After the divorce in 1992, there were no clashes and violence. On October 25, 1993, Mrs. Simpson called the police again: Former jealous husband was back to mock her. On June 12, 1994, 35-year-old Nicole, and Goldman, a young 25-year-old friend, were attacked and killed in Los Angeles. Only accused, Simpson was the protagonist of a spectacular flight in the car, broadcast live television. The nine months of the process that would end with absolution were followed with the breath suspended from all over the country and also the rest of the world.&nbsp;

